ddle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Quatremars was born in 1173, her father, Luke Quatremars, was 23 and her mother, Unknown, was 26. She had at least 2 sons with William de Charnells."},"et":{"1173–":"1173–Surnud","1168–1218":"1168–1218","1170–1234":"1170–1234","1173–Female":"1173–Surnud","1160–1195":"1160–1195","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1150–1196":"1150–1196","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1196":"1196","1240":"1240","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1148":"1148","1234":"1234","1168":"1168","1218":"1218","Elmesthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Elmesthorpe, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1173–":"1173–Kuollut","1168–1218":"1168–1218","1170–1234":"1170–1234","1173–Female":"1173–Kuollut","1160–1195":"1160–1195","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1150–1196":"1150–1196","1148–Female":"1148–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1190":"noin 1190","1196":"1196","1240":"1240","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1148":"1148","1234":"1234","1168":"1168","1218":"1218","Elmesthorpe, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Elmesthorpe, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1173–":"1173–Décédée","1168–1218":"1168–1218","1170–1234":"1170–1234","1173–Female":"1173–Décédée","1160–1195":"1160–1195","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1150–1196":"1150–1196","1148–Female":"1148–Décédée","1190":"1190","about 1190":"environ 1190","1196":"1196","1240"